&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Assignment: Home Services People Leader)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WelbeHealth is a value-based healthcare organization that’s transforming the future of senior care by providing an all-inclusive care option to our most vulnerable senior population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Associate Vice President, People Department (Assignment: Home Services People Leader) (AVP/HS) oversees the people function for the Home Services business of WelbeHealth. The AVP/HS creates and delivers the workforce and organization strategies, and supporting tactics, that accelerate the Home Services business. This role operates within a matrixed People model, partnering with People centers of excellence to deliver the day-to-day people services and programs, with shared accountability of outcomes in risk, compliance, performance, and growth. The AVP/HS partners with the Home Services senior leadership team to drive quality, productivity, and innovation on the full spectrum of the team member lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is different because the AVP/HS at WelbeHealth:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shapes the workforce that delivers care directly in the homes of vulnerable seniors, making a tangible impact on our participants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has the opportunity to sit where operational scale meets human-centered strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We care about our team members. That’s why we offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical insurance coverage (Medical, Dental, Vision)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work/life balance - We mean it! 17 days of personal time off (PTO), 12 holidays observed annually, and 6 sick days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K savings + match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive compensation package including base pay and bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And additional benefits!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On the day-to-day, you will: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage direct reports focused on key Home Services people work, such as employee and labor relations, as well as collaborate with other People experts in California and expansion states&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with business leaders on people and organization opportunities, challenges, restructuring, and transformations, driving business success by aligning people strategy with business objectives while fostering a culture of growth and adaptability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design, development, and use of people KPIs, both client-facing and for internal use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead proactive monitoring and strategics to mitigate employee and labor risk, working with operational leaders and evolving Home Services policies and practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the use of standard operating procedures to ensure consistent and scalable operations that meet client expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop trust-based relationships with Home Services leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent WelbeHealth at external PACE, home services, healthcare, and HR venues or associations, such as SHRM and ASHHRA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
