&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is different because&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drivers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;at&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WelbeHealth:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a meaningful impact&lt;strong&gt; - &lt;/strong&gt;every ride, interaction, and on-time arrival strengthens participant dignity, comfort, confidence, and connection to whole-person care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work as a team - drivers, dispatch, supervisors, and clinics stay aligned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow through learning - ongoing training builds skills to strengthen professional development, as well as service to participants and team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We care about our team members.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;That&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;why we offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical insurance coverage (Medical, Dental, Vision)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work/life balance - We mean it! 17 days of personal time off (PTO), 12 holidays observed annually, and 6 sick days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K savings + match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive compensation package including base pay, bonus, and equity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And additional benefits!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On the day-to-day, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to an assigned schedule of transporting PACE participants, ensuring high customer satisfaction&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all traffic and safety regulations while operating vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct comprehensive pre-inspections on assigned vehicles, including lift vans, ADA accessible minibuses, and ambulatory vehicles prior to the start of each shift&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist participants getting in and out of vehicles, as well as transferring participants in and out of wheelchairs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remain alert to pertinent input from other team members, participants, and caregivers, and promptly update the Transportation Supervisor of any changes in a participant’s condition or psychosocial status&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job requirements include:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma or equivalency; one (1) year of experience may be substituted in lieu of education&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Copy of recent vehicle insurance required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;All drivers must hold a valid driver’s license and meet company driving qualifications, including eligibility under our commercial auto insurance program. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Applicants must generally be at least 25 years old; candidates ages 23–24 may be considered based on driving history and other underwriting criteria. Drivers over age 70 may be required to provide current medical certification&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&

